The paper proposes a framework for explainable reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework involves analyzing an agent's history of interaction with the environment, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also describes how to create visual explanations of an agent's behavior, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper reports on a user study to evaluate the ability of humans to understand the agents' capabilities and limitations, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper's focus on improving the performance of agents suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO).
